M-Net has launched a pop-up channel dedicated to the Marvel universe on DStv. The channel is available to DStv Premium subscribers from 13-22 April. Each day of the week a film from the franchise will be screened in chronological order, starting with the 2008 film Iron Man. Movie screenings will run from 06:00 to midnight every day. In addition to 15 feature films, there will also be behind-the-scenes programming. Fans will also be able to watch a range of documentaries about the film franchise. The films on show on the channel include the Iron Man, Thor, Captain America, Guardians of the Galaxy, Spider-Man, The Avengers, and Ant-Man titles.